"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function does not return 1 at x=0 and 0 at x=1 for the sinc function defined as sinc(x) = sin(pi*x)/(pi*x). Instead, np.sinc is defined as sinc(x) = sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) when x!=0 and 1 when x=0. np.sinc(1) will not be exactly zero due to floating point precision.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7c7\\nassert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n---\\n8c8\\nassert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], np.sinc(1)), \\\"Results not equal to np.sinc(1)\\\"\"\n}"